ğŸ” GitHub API Integration Strategy
OAuth App vs GitHub App
Recommend: GitHub App (better permissions, org support)
Required Scopes
javascript
{
  contents: 'read/write',    // File operations
  actions: 'read/write',     // Trigger workflows
  codespaces: 'read/write',  // Manage codespaces
  gists: 'read/write'        // Pastebin feature
}
Rate Limiting Handling
Implement request queue
Cache responses with TanStack Query
Display rate limit status in UI
ğŸ“¦ Implementation Phases
Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)
 GitHub OAuth setup
 Repository list view
 Basic file explorer
 Monaco editor integration
Phase 2: Git Operations (Week 3-4)
 Push/Pull UI
 Commit creation
 Branch management
 Conflict resolution
Phase 3: Advanced Features (Week 5-6)
 Backup system
 GitHub Actions dashboard
 Pastebin/Gist integration
Phase 4: Polish (Week 7-8)
 Codespaces manager
 Search & analytics
 Performance optimization
 Documentation
ğŸ’¡ Unique Feature Ideas
Phase 0: Pre-Development Setup (GitHub App, dependencies, project structure)
Phase 1: Foundation & Core Infrastructure (API services, authentication, state management)
Phase 2: Git Operations Manager (push/pull, commits, branches, conflict resolution)
Phase 3: Repository File Manager & Backup System (explorer, automated backups, cloud storage)
Phase 4: Integrated Code Editor (Monaco Editor, multi-tab, git integration, split view)
Phase 5: Pastebin & Gist Manager (create/view/share snippets, password protection)
Phase 6: GitHub Actions Dashboard (workflows, real-time logs, visual builder, analytics)
Phase 7: Codespaces Manager (create/manage codespaces, resource monitoring, auto-shutdown)
Phase 8: UI/UX Polish (design system, animations, AI features, settings)